<doc id="924168" wikidata="Q5354792" url="?curid=924168" title="Elections in Panama">
<text>Panama elects on national level a head of state, i.e. the president, and a legislature. The president and the vice-president are elected on one ballot for a five-year term by the people. The National Assembly (&quot;Asamblea Nacional&quot;) has 71 members, elected for a five-year term in single-seat and multi-seat constituencies.

== Political culture ==
Panama has a multi-party system, with numerous parties in which no one party often has a chance of gaining power alone, and parties must work with each other to form coalition governments.

