<doc id="924302" wikidata="Q1487345" url="?curid=924302" title="GTOPO30">
<text>GTOPO30 is a digital elevation model for the world, developed by United States Geological Survey (USGS). It has a 30-arc second resolution (approximately 1¬†km), and is split into 33 tiles stored in the USGS DEM file format.

According to DTED and USGS DEM the absolute vertical accuracy of GTOP30 varies from ¬±30 meters.

==Gallery==
This map is derived from GTOPO30 data that describes the elevation of Earth&#x27;s terrain at intervals of 30 arcseconds (approximately 1¬†km). It uses hypsometric tints instead of contour lines to indicate elevation.

