<doc id="924457" wikidata="Q2313021" url="?curid=924457" title="Johnny Dixon (footballer)">
<text>John Thomas Dixon (10 December 1923 ‚Äì 20 January 2009) was an English footballer who played as an inside forward. He captained Aston Villa&#x27;s last FA Cup winning team in 1957.

Born in Hebburn, Dixon played for county league side Spennymoor United before he signed as a professional for Aston Villa shortly after the Second World War.

Dixon had Alzheimer&#x27;s disease, and died on 20 January 2009 in Good Hope Hospital, Sutton Coldfield.

==Career statistics==
==Honours==
Aston Villa
*FA Cup: 1956‚Äì57

